SBS football reporter Scott McIntyre tweeted 'inappropriate' comments on the day of Anzac Day  . 
  He accused the Australian diggers of committing war crimes and mocked their bravery  . 
  The tweets were met with a hashtag calling for him to be sacked  . 
  Minister for Communications Malcolm Turnbull called the comments 'despicable' The comments came on the 100th anniversary of the Battle of Gallipoli  . 
  McIntyre condemned the commemoration and accused the Anzacs of 'cultification of a foreign nation  . 
 